# Product Description / Presentation #

Conference Planning Crew â€” Multiâ€‘Agent AI Build Brief

Project Codename: OrchestrateX
Product description / presentation

OrchestrateX is a multiâ€‘agent conference planning platform that coordinates specialized AI agents to design, staff, budget, schedule, promote, and run conferences endâ€‘toâ€‘end. Agents collaborate to source venues, recruit speakers, negotiate sponsors, draft agendas, manage budgets, run marketing, handle registrations, and operate dayâ€‘of logisticsâ€”with humanâ€‘inâ€‘theâ€‘loop approvals and a complete audit trail. Outputs are grounded in documents, emails, and vendor data via Retrievalâ€‘Augmented Generation (RAG), and every decision is explainable with citations and costs.
What it does:
â€¢	Autoâ€‘generates a feasible plan (date windows, city shortlists, budget, highâ€‘level agenda) from an objective brief.
â€¢	Runs parallel agents: Venue Scout, Speaker Outreach, Sponsorship Manager, Budget Controller, Marketing Ops, Attendee Experience, Logistics & Travel, Risk & Compliance.
â€¢	Builds an agenda with tracks, assigns rooms, estimates capacity, and resolves conflicts with speaker/room constraints.
â€¢	Negotiates sponsor packages with counterâ€‘proposals and inventory (booths, stage time, branding) tracking.
â€¢	Launches campaigns, opens registration, manages tickets/pricing ladders, and monitors funnel KPIs.
â€¢	Operates a live Command Center on event days: session changes, push notifications, staffing tasks, incident runbooks.
Key features:
â€¢	Agent timeline board with checkpoints, dependencies, costs, and confidence bands.
â€¢	Schedule Builder (dragâ€‘andâ€‘drop) with conflict detection and room capacity modeling.
â€¢	Sponsor CRM with package templating, redline suggestions, and deliverables tracker.
â€¢	Budget console with scenario modeling and live variance vs. plan.
â€¢	RAGâ€‘grounded decisions with source snapshots from RFPs, vendor sheets, emails, and contracts.
Why teams love it:
â€¢	Compresses months of planning into weeks by parallelizing expert work safely.
â€¢	Improves sponsor revenue and attendee experience through dataâ€‘driven optimization.
â€¢	Keeps humans in control with clear approvals, citations, and cost impact for each decision.
Framework (and why)
LangGraph (orchestration) + LangChain (tools) + RAG (mandatory) with OpenAI + Claude. LangGraph provides deterministic, resumable, checkpointed multiâ€‘agent workflows with human approval gates, ideal for coordinating Venue, Speaker, Sponsor, Budget, Marketing, Logistics, and Risk agents. LangChain standardizes retrievers, tool calling, and tracing. RAG ensures plans and negotiations are grounded in RFPs, rate cards, contracts, and historical conference data. CrewAI can be used for early role prototyping, but production orchestration remains in LangGraph.
1. BACKEND ARCHITECTURE (extensive)
Core services (FastAPI â€¢ async SQLAlchemy 2.0 â€¢ Pydantic v2):
â€¢	Auth & Tenant: JWT (access/refresh), RBAC (admin, producer, coordinator, finance, sponsor_sales), optional SSO (OIDC/SAML), SCIM.
â€¢	Event Core: events, venues, rooms, tracks, sessions, speakers, sponsors, packages, deliverables, tasks, tickets, attendees.
â€¢	Knowledge & RAG: corpus ingestion (RFPs, vendor PDFs, contracts, emails, briefs), chunking, embeddings (pgvector), citations.
â€¢	Orchestrator (LangGraph): Brief â†’ Plan â†’ Parallel Agents (Venue/Speakers/Sponsors/Budget/Marketing/Logistics/Risk) â†’ HIL gates â†’ Finalize.
â€¢	Calendar & Email Sync: Google/Microsoft Graph connectors for holds, invites, and shared inbox triage.
â€¢	Ticketing & Payments: ticket types, pricing ladders, promo codes; Stripe checkout + webhooks; registration flows.
â€¢	Vendor Connectors: mapping for hotels/venues (RFP portals), A/V, catering, signage, streaming platforms.
â€¢	Budget & Contracts: baseline budget, PO/Invoice lifecycle, contract templates, tracked changes and approvals.
â€¢	Comms & Notifications: WebSockets for live updates; templated emails/SMS/push; announcement queues.
â€¢	Audit & Governance: approvals, versioning, rationale logs, exportable audit trails.
Pipelines (LangGraph subgraphs):
â€¢	Planning: parse brief â†’ city/date shortlist â†’ capacity & budget model â†’ draft tracks.
â€¢	Venue: collect RFPs â†’ compare AV/catering/min spend â†’ negotiate holds â†’ contract redlines â†’ approval.
â€¢	Speakers: source bios â†’ outreach variants â†’ hold times â†’ contract â†’ travel & session assignment.
â€¢	Sponsors: package design â†’ outreach â†’ counterâ€‘proposal loop â†’ deliverables & invoicing.
â€¢	Marketing: persona definition â†’ calendar â†’ creative variants â†’ channel mix â†’ conversion targets.
